web sites & publishing information resources & technology irt stanford university school of medicine stanford school of medicine information resources & technology irt search this site only stanford medical sites ways to give find a person alumni lane library ways to give find a person web site development quick help request a new site request an existing site be redesigned request editing access to an existing site irt develops and supports the overall public web presence for the school of medicine and stanford hospital & clinics we work on behalf of the leadership at both institutions to create a flexible framework that can be leveraged by all departments and units within stanford medicine we support a broad array of web sites which in aggregate total over 300000 web pages and work collaboratively with a diverse community of local web authors we offer departments and web authors not only expert advice and execution in architecture and design we make sure that your web site incorporates the latest technologies core services irt built and maintains a solid public web infrastructure that can house and support the many individual web needs throughout stanford medicine this infrastrucure includes a solid design that allows individual units to apply unique branding to their sites while still keeping it within the stanford medicine family a set of standard tools for individual units to maintain their sites training and support to those web authors that are maintaining sites a highly available hosting environment a set of web site enhancement tools specific to the stanford medicine site there are so many possibilities for features devices technologies and layouts that we created a model site to help you explore them on an ongoing basis irt web & new media promotes and encourages collaboration of web users and publishers of stanford medicine through web author community gatherings web help web training and an email list start a new project with us you are here current tab 